  "full_text_flowing_modernisation_text_block": "Adhem Beg Efendi arrived auspiciously at the Sublime Porte on his official mission, and upon performing the necessities...\n...of reception and honoring, and executing the ceremonies of glorification and respect, and after the acts of kissing [the document] and greeting,\nit was opened and read; and by adorning the ears of friendship with its content—which is joined to obedience—\nat its conclusion, the Prayer-Reciter Efendi raised his hands to the Court of God, and [for] the person of high attributes...\n...of the Grand Vizier, as well as Their Excellencies the other illustrious ministers, and all the statesmen and servants,\nsaying \"Amen\" with perfect sincerity, the charitable prayers in which we are assiduous...\n...for the increase of the life, majesty, and prosperity of His Excellency the Refuge of the Caliphate, and consecutively the prayers...\n...for the good success of the Vice-regency were paid and performed; and the auspicious outcome...\n...of the Noble Rescript, familiar with the majesty of His Imperial Excellency, polishing the sight of the elite and commoners [alike],\nin order to be [so], and for blessing and benediction, and to gladden the hearts of the people, it has been printed and represented exactly in this place also.\n[It has been made].\nCOPY OF THE IMPERIAL RESCRIPT\nMy zealous Vizier and loyal Marshal, Hüsrev Muhammed Pasha! My glorious father,\nof abundant praiseworthy traits, His Excellency Sultan Mahmud Khan, upon his passing by the decree of God Exalted,\nand with the transfer of the Throne of the Caliphate—helper of majesty—to my Imperial Person by inheritance and entitlement,\nall kingdoms and servants have been committed and entrusted to my Royal charge from the side of the Merciful [God].\nBecause this has been ordained, in thanks for this glorious favor, and relying upon the help of the favor of His Excellency\nthe Creator, and the aid of the spirituality of His Excellency the Prophet, it is incumbent upon the debit of my kingly zeal\nto administer all affairs in their worthy axis, conforming to the Noble Sharia,\nand regarding the matter of acquiring the peace and comfort of all the people, the poor, the weak, and the subjects;\npreferring its execution to the pleasures of my own Imperial self, and indeed counting it a cause of pleasure and pride,\nand since the good attainment of this Imperial desire of ours—by the success of the Exalted [God]—\nappears dependent on the presence of a person of zealous attributes, experienced and veteran in every state and manner, in the service of the Grand Vizierate;\nand since you, having acquired fame and distinction in our Exalted State for many years through proof of loyalty and zeal in great difficulties,\nand having acquired the name 'Doyen of Viziers',\nand being found among the most loyal of my Sublime Sultanate; I have selected and appointed you with independence,\nby my correct Royal idea, to the glorious station of the Absolute Grand Vizierate and Deputyship,\nwith comprehensive supervision over internal and external affairs, financial and military interests, and in short, all particulars.\nYou also, knowing the value and thanks of this glorious Imperial favor of mine,\nand holding fast with perfection to the strong rope of the Purified Sharia,\nand observing the ceremonies of unity and accord with all my illustrious ministers,\nmay you hasten to the good settlement and execution of all affairs of the kingdoms and servants, upon the requirement of your independence.\nMay His Excellency the Truth [God] make you, and those together with you who render service and loyalty to my religion and state,\nsuccessful and dear in both worlds. Amen.\nThe Noble Kiswah of the Kaaba the Great, which had been sent previously having been woven and manufactured in the Court of the Abode of Majesty,\nand placed and hung at the station of the angel-servants; the Ancient Noble Kiswah,\nupon the return of the Superintendent of the Imperial Surre this time, arrived auspiciously.\nTherefore, in accordance with the Imperial Will of His Majesty the King which pertained to the twenty-fourth day of the mentioned month, a Saturday,\nall the illustrious ministers of the Exalted State and the Masters of the Procession,\ngathered and halted at the place named Ayrılık Fountain situated in Üsküdar;\nand while they were manifesting longing and waiting for the honor of the arrival of the Noble Blessed Kiswah,\nthe Blessed Kiswah appeared, casting light upon the mentioned place...",
  "summary": "This document, dated July 11, 1839, records the formal reading of an Imperial Rescript (Hatt-ı Hümâyûn) at the Sublime Porte following the death of Sultan Mahmud II and the accession of Sultan Abdülmecid I. The text begins by describing the ceremonial arrival of Adhem Bey Efendi to deliver the rescript, followed by prayers for the new Sultan. The core of the document is the Rescript itself, addressed to Koca Hüsrev Mehmed Pasha. It confirms Hüsrev Pasha's appointment as Grand Vizier (Sadrazam) with absolute authority (vekâlet-i mutlaqa). The young Sultan emphasizes his commitment to Sharia law, justice, and the welfare of all subjects, instructing the Grand Vizier to ensure unity among ministers and effective administration. The final section reports on a separate religious ceremony in Üsküdar at the Ayrılık Fountain, marking the return of the 'Ancient Kiswah' (the old covering of the Kaaba) brought back by the Superintendent of the Imperial Surre."
